From 94010f52e7afee1b4a9a03120c05ffa2ca639f7d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mikhail Malyshev <mike.malyshev@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 11:38:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] hw/isa/lpc_ich9: add x-device-id property to spoof PCH ID
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add an x-device-id property on the QEMU ICH9-LPC device that
overrides the PCI device-ID register at config offset 0x02 when set.
Default 0 means "leave at class default 0x2918".

Set on the QEMU command line via:

    -global ICH9-LPC.x-device-id=0xa082

Why:  the proprietary IntelGopDriver in OEM firmware (vendor
option-ROMs we deploy via /persist/vault/gop/<rom>) does PCH
detection by reading the LPC bridge device ID at PCI 00:1f.0 and
refuses to bind to the iGPU if the value isn't on its real-hardware
allow-list.  q35's emulated ICH9 default 0x2918 is never on that
allow-list, so without this spoof the proprietary GOP path silently
refuses to initialise and the physical monitor stays dark during
the UEFI phase.

The OSS path (bundled IgdAssignmentDxe in VfioIgdPkg) does not need
this — it has no PCH whitelist.  In fact applying the spoof on the
OSS path actively confuses the Windows display driver on at least
RPL-P (different PCH ID changes its quirk-table path → tile-mode
mismatch on scanout), so the kvm.go side that emits this -global
gates the spoof to only fire when a proprietary GOP ROM is in use.

Implementation:

  - struct ICH9LPCState gains a uint32_t device_id_override.
  - DEFINE_PROP_UINT32 "x-device-id" exposes it on the QOM type,
    default 0 (= use class default).
  - ich9_lpc_realize() applies the override via
    pci_config_set_device_id() when non-zero, before any other code
    consults the device-ID field.

Risks: spoofing a PCH that disagrees with QEMU's q35 ACPI tables /
emulated power-management may upset guest ACPI / SMI / power
management.  Operator-supplied per-platform — see id.json schema
on the EVE side.

Signed-off-by: Mikhail Malyshev <mike.malyshev@gmail.com>
---
 hw/isa/lpc_ich9.c             | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 include/hw/southbridge/ich9.h |  9 +++++++++
 2 files changed, 28 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tools/qemu-xen/hw/isa/lpc_ich9.c b/tools/qemu-xen/hw/isa/lpc_ich9.c
index bd727b2320..00b7942cc3 100644
--- a/tools/qemu-xen/hw/isa/lpc_ich9.c
+++ b/tools/qemu-xen/hw/isa/lpc_ich9.c
@@ -697,6 +697,16 @@ static void ich9_lpc_realize(PCIDevice *d, Error **errp)
     ISABus *isa_bus;
     uint32_t irq;
 
+    /*
+     * Apply the optional x-device-id override before any code uses the
+     * device-ID field of PCI config space.  See struct ICH9LPCState for
+     * the rationale (diagnostic spoofing for proprietary GOP / SA
+     * drivers).
+     */
+    if (lpc->device_id_override != 0) {
+        pci_config_set_device_id(d->config, lpc->device_id_override);
+    }
+
     if ((lpc->smi_host_features & BIT_ULL(ICH9_LPC_SMI_F_CPU_HOT_UNPLUG_BIT)) &&
         !(lpc->smi_host_features & BIT_ULL(ICH9_LPC_SMI_F_CPU_HOTPLUG_BIT))) {
         /*
@@ -826,6 +836,15 @@ static Property ich9_lpc_properties[] = {
                       ICH9_LPC_SMI_F_CPU_HOTPLUG_BIT, true),
     DEFINE_PROP_BIT64("x-smi-cpu-hotunplug", ICH9LPCState, smi_host_features,
                       ICH9_LPC_SMI_F_CPU_HOT_UNPLUG_BIT, true),
+    /*
+     * x-device-id: override the LPC's PCI device ID register.  Defaults
+     * to 0 which means "use class default 0x2918".  Set to a real-hardware
+     * PCH device ID (e.g. 0xa082 for a TGL-H WM490 PCH) to placate
+     * proprietary firmware drivers that whitelist real PCH models during
+     * PCH detection.  Diagnostic / debug knob — using a value disagreeing
+     * with QEMU's q35 ACPI tables risks ACPI / power-management mismatches.
+     */
+    DEFINE_PROP_UINT32("x-device-id", ICH9LPCState, device_id_override, 0),
     DEFINE_PROP_END_OF_LIST(),
 };
 
diff --git a/tools/qemu-xen/include/hw/southbridge/ich9.h b/tools/qemu-xen/include/hw/southbridge/ich9.h
index fd01649d04..0347a4e6fe 100644
--- a/tools/qemu-xen/include/hw/southbridge/ich9.h
+++ b/tools/qemu-xen/include/hw/southbridge/ich9.h
@@ -54,6 +54,15 @@ struct ICH9LPCState {
     uint8_t rst_cnt;
     MemoryRegion rst_cnt_mem;
 
+    /*
+     * Optional override for the LPC's PCI device ID, exposed as the
+     * x-device-id property.  Used to spoof real-hardware PCH IDs for
+     * proprietary Intel GOP / SA drivers that gate on the PCH model.
+     * 0 = use class default (PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_ICH9_8 / 0x2918).
+     * Diagnostic only — disagrees with QEMU's q35 ACPI tables.
+     */
+    uint32_t device_id_override;
+
     /* SMI feature negotiation via fw_cfg */
     uint64_t smi_host_features;       /* guest-invisible, host endian */
     uint8_t smi_host_features_le[8];  /* guest-visible, read-only, little
